		<p><b>Harley Martin Kilgore (1893-1956), Senator, Papers</b></p>
		<p>Senator Harley Martin Kilgore (b. 1893) served in the U.S. Senate from 1940-1956. He served on the Special Committee Investigating the National Defense Program, popularly known as the Truman Committee, which investigated defense spending during World War II. It was one of the most productive investigating committees in history and saved millions of dollars. Kilgore headed up numerous investigations, many of which related to steel production and ship building. The files contain hearings, memoranda, correspondence, and photographs.</p>
		<p><a href="https://archives.lib.wvu.edu/repositories/2/resources/4778">View Harley Martin Kilgore finding aid</a></p>
		<br>
		<p><b>Arch A. Moore Jr. papers</b></p>
		<p>Arch Alfred Moore Jr. (b. 1923) served two consecutive terms as Governor of West Virginia from 1969-1977 and a third term from 1985-1989. He was an unsuccessful candidate for reelection for governor in 1988. Previously, he was elected as a Republican to five terms in the United States House of Representatives, serving from January 3, 1957-January 3, 1969. He was not a candidate for reelection to the Ninety-first Congress in 1968. He died on January 7, 2015, in Charleston, WV. The Arch A. Moore Jr. papers document his service as governor of West Virginia and in the U.S. Congress.
		</p>
		<p><a href="https://archives.lib.wvu.edu/repositories/2/resources/965">View Arch A. Moore Jr. finding aid</a></p>
