		<p><b>Howard Sutherland, Senator, Women's Suffrage Papers</b></p>
		<p>Howard Sutherland (b. 1865) served a short time in the U.S. Senate (1916-1923), and served as chairman of the Committee on the Census and Committee on Enrolled Bills. He received a considerable amount of correspondence related to women’s suffrage, including the Bristow-Mondell House Resolution and the Susan B. Anthony Amendment. Correspondents are individuals and organizations located in West Virginia and nationally.</p>
